\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Look at God's concern...\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\tx1660\tx2160\pardeftab720\li2160\fi-2160\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl2\cf5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Our temptation is to make decisions based on what we 
\f0\b SEE
\f1\b0  and not what God 
\f0\b SAYS
\f1\b0 .\cf2 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \
\pard\tx1660\tx2160\pardeftab720\li2160\fi-2160\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl2\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 I mean it would have been easy for Odysseus to look out into the ocean and not see anything dangerous.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls3\ilvl2\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Or he could have waited until he saw the danger...that is what most of us.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls3\ilvl2\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 But the reality is that too often by the time we see the danger it is too late.\'a0 \uc0\u8232 \
\ls3\ilvl2\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 One of the verses we looked at last week was 1 Cor 6:18 where Paul says RUN from temptation.\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\tx2380\tx2880\pardeftab720\li2880\fi-2880\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl3\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The question I want to ask you today is are you doing that?\uc0\u8232 \
